President Cyril Ramaphosa says the action taken by the police during student protests in Braamfontein is unwarranted. eNCA's Nkosazana Dambuza filed this report. #DStv403​ #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - ANC officials are set to meet Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande on Friday. ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule, says student demands are legitimate and consistent with ANC policy following days of protests over financial exclusions. READ: Amnesty International SA calls for ban on use of rubber bullets Meanwhile, Nzimande says funding for students has been prioritised.
 
“Cabinet agreed that funding should re-prioritised from the budget of higher education and training to ensure that all qualifying students can receive funding for the 2021 academic year.” President Cyril Ramaphosa says the action taken by the police during student protests in Braamfontein is unwarranted. Watch the video above for more details.